    "json_schema_template": "{\n  \"review_id\": ${review_id},\n  \"sentiment\": \"${sentiments}\",\n  \"sentiment_score\": 0.8, // FLOAT from -1.0 (very negative) to 1.0 (very positive)\n  \"confidence\": 0.9, // FLOAT from 0.0 to 1.0\n  \"issue\": \"specific complaint or null (MAX 8 WORDS)\",\n  \"churn_risk\": \"${churn_risks}\",\n  \"pain_point_category\": \"${pain_points}\",\n  \"root_cause\": \"brief underlying problem (MAX 5 WORDS)\",\n  \"feature_request\": \"Specific user request or 'None' (MAX 10 WORDS)\",\n  \"trending_theme\": \"Most common theme or 'None' (MAX 5 WORDS)\",\n  \"emerging_theme\": \"Uncommon theme or 'None' (MAX 5 WORDS)\",\n  \"intent\": \"${intents}\",\n  \"emotions\": [\"Satisfaction\", \"Disappointment\"], // ARRAY of 1 to 3 items from the EMOTIONS LIST\n  \"urgency\": \"${urgency}\",\n  \"user_segment\": \"${segments}\",\n  \"domain_insight\": \"One concise, vertical-specific observation based on '${vertical}' focus (MAX 15 WORDS)\" // NEW FIELD\n}",
    "prompt_template": "TASK: Analyze the single app review below. Your output **MUST ONLY** be a **minimal, single-line JSON object** that adheres strictly to the provided SCHEMA and RULES.\n\nVERTICAL FOCUS: ${vertical_upper} (Focus on the following concepts for 'domain_insight': ${focus_keywords})${custom_instructions}\nEMOTIONS LIST (for 'emotions' field): ${emotions_list}\n\nOUTPUT RULES:\n1. Output MUST ONLY be a valid, single-line JSON object. No markdown, no pre-amble, no conversational text.\n2. Adhere strictly to the JSON SCHEMA and word/list constraints.\n3. **CRITICAL JSON RULE (NEW):** Ensure ALL string values, especially 'issue', 'root_cause', 'domain_insight', are correctly JSON-escaped. Internal double quotes must be \\\", and internal backslashes must be \\\\. Do NOT use raw newlines or tabs.\n4. **SENTIMENT SCORE GUIDANCE:** Map the user's 1-5 Rating to the sentiment_score float (e.g., Rating 5/4 -> Score > 0.5. Rating 3 -> Score between -0.5 and 0.5. Rating 2/1 -> Score < -0.5).\n5. 'emotions' MUST be an array of 1 to 3 strings from the EMOTIONS LIST.\n6. Categories MUST match the lists provided in the JSON SCHEMA.\n7. **Domain Insight:** MUST relate to the '${vertical_upper}' vertical and its focus keywords.\n\nJSON SCHEMA: ${json_schema}\n\nREVIEW CONTENT: \nRating: ${rating}/5\nText: ${content}",
    "quick_json_schema_template": "{\n  \"review_id\": ${review_id},\n  \"sentiment\": \"${sentiments}\",\n  \"sentiment_score\": 0.8, // FLOAT from -1.0 (very negative) to 1.0 (very positive)\n  \"confidence\": 0.9, // FLOAT from 0.0 to 1.0\n  \"churn_risk\": \"${churn_risks}\"\n}",
    "quick_prompt_template": "TASK: Quickly analyze the sentiment and health of this app review. Output **ONLY** a **minimal, single-line JSON object**.\n\nOUTPUT RULES:\n1. Output MUST ONLY be a valid, single-line JSON object. No markdown, no explanations.\n2. **SENTIMENT SCORE:** Map the 1-5 Rating to sentiment_score (Rating 5/4 -> >0.5, Rating 3 -> -0.5 to 0.5, Rating 2/1 -> <-0.5).\n3. **CHURN RISK:** 'high' if user expresses cancellation/refund intent, 'medium' for strong negative sentiment, 'low' otherwise.\n4. **CONFIDENCE:** 0.8-1.0 for clear sentiment, 0.5-0.8 for moderate clarity, below 0.5 for ambiguous.\n\nJSON SCHEMA: ${json_schema}\n\nREVIEW:\nRating: ${rating}/5\nText: ${content}"
}